{"key":"processedPost-6172980","value":{"id":6172980,"first":6172930,"last":6173270,"when":1160960413,"utime":"10/16/06 04:00 AM","content":"The answer is not peroxide, but to inoculate with clean culture.  The current fad of making LC directly from spores is responsible for many failures.  Personally, I'd never consider making an LC with anything but mycelium that I had ran across the flat plane of a petri dish to check for contaminants.  Build a glovebox and make up some agar plates to check and isloate your strains on.  Inoculate grains with an agar wedge, then do a grain to grain transfer to increase mass.<br />RR","title":"Re: Peroxide grain formulas please","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}